author: Jim Kleinpeter, NOLA.com | The Times-Picayune
title: LSU moves up to No. 6 in AP Top 25 poll
text:
LSU moved up on spot to No. 6 in the latest Associated Press Top 25 college football poll and stayed at No. 5 in the Amway coaches Top 25 poll released Sunday.
LSU (5-0, 3-0 in SEC) beat South Carolina 45-24 on Saturday and movd up when Michigan State dropped from No. 4 to No. 7. LSU got one of the 62 first-place votes for the third consecutive week in the coaches poll.
Read more: Leonard Fournette Heisman Watch after South Carolina.
Ohio State held on to the top spot in both polls followed by Baylor and TCU. Urah moved up to No. 4 in the AP poll and Clemson was No. 5. The coaches poll had Michigan State and LSU rounding out the top 5, followed by Clemson, Utah, Florida State, Alabama and Texas A&M.
LSU's next opponent, Florida, moved up one spot to No. 11 in the coaches poll and three spots in the AP poll to No. 8. The SEC had five teams in the coaches top 12 and five in the AP TOP 13. There were no other SEC teams in the top 25 after having 10 at one point.
